First Lady Melania Trump hosted a private meeting with First Lady Fabiana Rosales of Venezuela at Mar-a-Lago in Florida. Mrs. Trump expressed her concern for the Venezuelan people and reiterated the US administration's commitment to supporting the new leadership in Venezuela. The two first ladies discussed various issues, including the impact of the crises on Venezuelan children and how Fabiana Rosales plans to provide relief. Melania Trump emphasized the importance of freedom for children and expressed support for Fabiana Rosales and her husband, President Juan Guaido, in their efforts to restore democracy in Venezuela.